f the international advisory board of sebi securities and exchange board of india and undertaking the position of independent director at principal which will become effective on august 7 speaking of his nonexecutive role at principal he said “they principal serve  million clients from offices in  countries including several here in asia this will require me to visit the us around five times per year to attend board meetings”       mr pickerell admitted that there is a possibility that he will look into undertaking more directorship positions in the future but said that in order to maintain work from interfering into his new life which includes hiking golf and gardening he has set a goal of “being busy with such nonexecutive activities only around  of the time”   after receiving his mba from harvard and being hired by jardine matheson to set up their jardine fleming taiwan office in  mr pickerell pioneered the mutual fund in taiwan first selling to expatriates then to locals then eventually convincing taiwan banks to act as intermediaries to sell his fund proficient in mandarin chinese he did not have to overcome the language barrier as a result he transformed the mutual fund from an offshore product into a popular choice among retail investors in taiwan concurrently helping jf become a monopoly player in the market in  mr pickerell also spearheaded the us million huaan innovation fund the first openended mutual fund to be introduced in china managed by the local huaan financial firm the fund invested in rmbdenominated class ashares highlights a tangle of political problems focus government pension fund gpf thailand etienne bouaslaurent to succeed stuart harrison as axa hong kong ceo navigating future forward change from concept to reality clos back on investors’ radars navigating future forward change taiwan asset managers’ fee income at fiveyear high china signals cautions approach to tightening says fitch pe panorama calpers looking to move into direct investment territory boaml investors most underweight on us stocks since  japan’s definedbenefit pension funds boost exposure to alternatives most popular fullerton bolsters investment leadership team etienne bouaslaurent to succeed stuart harrison as axa hong kong ceo china’s inclusion in msci doesn’t erase investment risk pe panorama calpers to pull out of pe japan and australia ink fintech pact korea’s kic expected to open new office in singapore manulife gets green light to operate trust business in philippines pinebridge lures lisa wang from ssga enter the vortex mirae asset life set to seal deal for  stake in vietnamese insurer about us   advertise   editorial   contacts   terms of service   privacy information   site help   enewsletter    rss to subscribe to asia asset management magazine call us at  7  during business hours am to pm hkt or click here  7 asiapacific media limited all rights reserved this material may not be published broadcast rewritten or redistributed in any form without prior authorisation produced by javacatz back to home member login enjoy unlimited access to wwwasiaassetcom quickly growing article database not a asiaassetcom member yet enjoy limited time free access just fill in your profile with login id and password and youll be all set register now already an asiaassetcom member log in now login id or email address  password  forgot your password remember me on this computer log in  please wait  7 asiapacific media limited subscription alert please renewupgrade now  7 asiapacific media limited close in  seconds   forbidden access is denied server error   forbidden access is denied you do not have permission to view this directory or page using the credentials that you supplied